                            <comment id="13295370" author="thelabdude" created="Fri, 15 Jun 2012 00:12:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, so here&apos;s a solution to this problem. It really made a huge difference in the size of the output in our environment. With this patch, the output was reduced to a few Gigs as opposed to 4+ TBs!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I only applied this to the &quot;pw&quot; style output as it probably isn&apos;t useful for the &quot;v&quot; style output. Also, the default value is Double.MAX_VALUE since a default of 1.0 would imply you were using cosine distance.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
